holland@CS.ColoState.EDU writes in article <Sep29.200145.78889@yuma.ACNS.ColoState.EDU>:
> 
> I know that it is possible to hide an encrypted message in the least
> significant bits of a file like a picture file.  Does anyone have a
> program that will hide a PGP message in a .gif file?

GIF files use a (VGA like) palette, that might make it much more difficult to
add invisible information. Using e.g. TGA (most preferably 24bit) would
leave much more space for hidden information.

